2026-05-29 | Minimum Element After Digit Sum Replacement

	Question
Return the minimum element after all replacements.
	Approach
1.	Traverse each number in nums.
2.	Compute its digit sum.
3.	Keep track of the minimum digit sum seen.
4.	Return the minimum.
	Time Complexity
	O(n × digits)
	Space Complexity
	O(1)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    int digitSum(int x){
        int sum = 0;
        while(x > 0){
            sum += x % 10;
            x /= 10;
        }
        return sum;
    }
    int minElement(vector<int>& nums) {
        int ans = INT_MAX;
        for(int x : nums){
            ans = min(ans, digitSum(x));
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
	Key Insight
There is no need to actually modify the array.
Simply compute the digit sum of each element and keep the smallest one.
